The `File` methods that set various attributes: `setExecutable`, `setReadable`, `setReadOnly`, `setWritable` are replaced by the `Files` method [setAttribute(Path, String, Object, LinkOption...)][1].

**Usage Example:**

```java
public void setFileAttributes() throws IOException {
  Path path = ...

  UserPrincipal user = path.getFileSystem().getUserPrincipalLookupService().lookupPrincipalByName(&quot;user&quot;);
  AclFileAttributeView view = Files.getFileAttributeView(path, AclFileAttributeView.class);
  AclEntry entry = AclEntry.newBuilder()
          .setType(ALLOW)
          .setPrincipal(user)
          .setPermissions(Set.of(READ_DATA, EXECUTE, WRITE_DATA))
          .build();
  List&lt;AclEntry&gt; acl = view.getAcl();
  acl.add(0, entry);

  Files.setAttribute(path, &quot;acl:acl&quot;, acl);
}
```

See [AclFileAttributeView][2] for more details.


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/13/docs/api/java.base/java/nio/file/Files.html#setAttribute(java.nio.file.Path,java.lang.String,java.lang.Object,java.nio.file.LinkOption...)
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/13/docs/api/java.base/java/nio/file/attribute/AclFileAttributeView.html

